<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>No, I don&#39;t want to hear &quot;Debussy&quot; &quot;Rach&quot; or &quot;Ravel&quot; </p> <p>I&#39;m talking about pieces that are really....Story based. Pieces of Impressionistic and expressionistic character that convey a picture, or a feeling (preferably based on the titles of such pieces) </p> <p>I just listened to Frank Bridges &quot;Fairy Tale&quot; Suite, and Baines&#39; preludes, and I must know more similar pieces </p> <p>Instruments of pieces I want is for primarily piano, but either Cello, Flute, or Harp works too.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/PXtreme_YT"> /u/PXtreme_YT </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/133atlp/any_composers_similar_to_frank_bridge_or_william/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/133atlp/any_composers_similar_to_frank_bridge_or_william/">[comments]</a></span>